I '''Daniel J. Barrett''' (mibait [[Nobiembri 6]], [[1963]]) metung yang [[talasulat]], software engineer, web site maintainer, [[talatigtig]], ampong [[Usenet]] personality. Bantug ya kareng kayang aklat keng technology, ding kayang obra kambe nang progressive rock band [[Gentle Giant]], ampo ing kayang imaginary computer game [[Blazemonger|BLAZEMONGER]].

==Sinulat==
I Barrett mekasulat ya kareng mapilan a aklat tungkul keng technical a computer a paksa. Ing pekabantug iyapin ing ''Linux Pocket Guide''<ref>USA Linux Users Group, [http://usalug.org/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=4638 Book Review: Linux Pocket Guide]</ref>and  ''SSH, The Secure Shell: The Definitive Guide''<ref>Unix Review, [http://www.unixreview.com/documents/s=1236/urm0104d/ Review by Ben Rothke]</ref>. Ding kayang aklat melikas la keng [[Czech]], [[French]], [[Aleman]], [[Hungarian]], [[Japanese]], [[Mandarin]], [[Polish]], ampong [[Russian]].

==Blazemonger==
In the 1990s, Barrett created the concept of [[Blazemonger|BLAZEMONGER]], <ref>[http://groups.google.com/group/comp.sys.amiga/browse_thread/thread/1557d709264598b5/9d94bec024a21206 First BLAZEMONGER article, December 8, 1990]</ref> an imaginary computer game that spoofed the computing industry, and wrote approximately 100 articles about it.<ref>[http://www.blazemonger.com/BM/ BLAZEMONGER archive]</ref>

